Prodorsum (
Fig. 7
A). Cerotegument granular, smaller granules next to anterior notogastral border. Rostrum nearly triangular in dorsal view, slightly projecting anteroventrally in lateral view. Rostrum demarcated from remainder of prodorsum by obvious transverse ridge. Pair of two converging, slender lamellar ridges in slightly lateral position, reaching from bothridium to lamellar seta. Rostral seta (
ro
) robust, setiform, smooth (approx. 15 µm). Lamellar seta (
le
) simple, short and smooth (approx. 7 µm). Interlamellar seta (
in
) simple (approx. 12 µm), exobothridial seta (
ex
) minute. Sunk bothridium, i.e. not strongly protruding, borders not clearly defined; orifice narrow and circular. A semicircular depression directly anterior of bothridium. Sensillus long (approx. 60 µm), slightly fusiform and distally pectinate.
